Multiple gate MOSFETs have emerged as the most promising contenders [1] amongst various next generation semiconductor devices. A symmetric Double Gate (SDG) MOSFET is a variant of multigate MOSFETs, which is considered to be an ideal device that can be scaled beyond the bulk CMOS limit [2]. Mathematical modelling of MOSFETs has always been a challenging task whenever technology node and device generations change with respect to device channel length \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
