				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$L$$\end{document}L. As the device channel lengths are scaled down from micrometer to nanometer regime, the carrier transport behaviour changes from drift–diffusive to ballistic [3]. In the nanoscale regime, initially the velocity saturation and then the source injection velocity limit become the major physical effects that limit the drain current. Figure 1 presents the various transport phenomena and occurrence of different physical effects when the device channel length \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
